<subSubSection id="904DB04027966FF6F888992DA647A20A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclatural history">
<paragraph id="5ECEF8B560C718BFAFE213FFA5CE52D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Nomenclatural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1A290E6A01AC7D3370CFED41715F46B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
It has been widely accepted that the original place of publication of the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="34652F0ABB72193AB07B63AA1FB93062" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0300343C554F1766849353AE125B3A3A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is &quot;Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane 
<normalizedToken id="2FCA38BE4C2B0DFBFC2D390982E6D1B8" originalValue="Françoise”">Francoise&quot;</normalizedToken>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="2F61D9615A201B2C65FA82596E7854A5" author="Aublet, JBCF" journalOrPublisher="Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Aublet, JBCF, 1775. Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1). Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" title="Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1)." year="1775">Aublet (1775)</bibRefCitation>
. Nonetheless, Aublet never clearly states to be proposing a new genus. This seems to follow his 
<normalizedToken id="11E4FCE1C00C32E0D4BFE2676AAE7549" originalValue="publication’s">publication's</normalizedToken>
formatting, where none of the new taxa present any explicit statement indicating that they are newly proposed. At the end of the Latin diagnosis and French comments, 
<bibRefCitation id="6F7D15B8DBDA39291380193806AAA391" author="Aublet, JBCF" journalOrPublisher="Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Aublet, JBCF, 1775. Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1). Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" title="Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1)." year="1775">Aublet (1775</bibRefCitation>
: 35) mentions that his new species differs from the one described by 
<bibRefCitation id="14C9439A9B34EB6BB8AFA1562A535F28" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">Loefling (1758)</bibRefCitation>
due to its &quot;fine stems and leaves furnished with hairs, blue flowers, and oval and acute petals&quot;. This statement makes it clear that Aublet had access to 
<normalizedToken id="F21FFE59AA265DD371C65272F629633E" originalValue="Loefling’s">Loefling's</normalizedToken>
publication (1758) and knew of the description of his new genus 
<taxonomicName id="7BACBCDA522506BD51D7F034E94DAE60" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="419758C8855F615715DBD12F68AE40F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, 
<bibRefCitation id="14C530F3EA221390776E17FAF75A7726" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" author="Dorr, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1245 - 1262" refId="B10" refString="Dorr, LJ, Wiersema, JH, 2010. Names of American vascular plants published in Loefling's Iter Hispanicum (1758) and its German translation (1766). Taxon 59 (4): 1245 - 1262, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" title="Names of American vascular plants published in Loefling's Iter Hispanicum (1758) and its German translation (1766)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.594022" volume="59" year="2010">Dorr and Wiersema (2010)</bibRefCitation>
give the final support to our interpretation when they explain that in several instances, 
<bibRefCitation id="241FC3706C716CEBDF1B108D5898A3A9" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">Loefling (1758)</bibRefCitation>
cited a genus published earlier by Linnaeus or P. Browne, followed by a full stop, (an) alternative generic name(s) and a description. The authors also point out that, on some occasions, this formatting has been misinterpreted as the proposal of 
<normalizedToken id="88F3A12FCB719B9F9D44E378B343E69C" originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
names (i.e., binary combinations), which they are not. That was the case of 
<taxonomicName id="D0384B91038D71A2C9EEF4C5D5229F4F" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7962D64FBD6E0001A6CC7768309C048" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loefl., which was misinterpreted as representing a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="EB4D5DFF9E2B5A9603CE4BDF767C5D32" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ixia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ixia xiphidium" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiphidium">
<emphasis id="1F036B9CC420C28035E5E9BF464E5659" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ixia xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loefl. (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="FBEFFE00A88320379B0BF95A6D94FC71" author="Maas, PJM" journalOrPublisher="Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 44" refId="B27" refString="Maas, PJM, Maas-van de Kamer, H, 1993. Haemodoraceae. Fl. Neotropica 61: 1 - 44" title="Haemodoraceae. Fl." volume="61" year="1993">Maas and Maas-van de Kamer 1993</bibRefCitation>
), instead of the publication of a new genus. Thus, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A756D612150CF5204CDC040DE1A9ECEE" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="39B7E72911953C2E19942195749C3C1D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="C2C09D6327CFFA8C8697D0C213F14569" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">Loefling (1758)</bibRefCitation>
, without the inclusion of any species. The proposal of 
<taxonomicName id="316878394B5670E2B98C0701E794FF83" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F9089C71DB22A962F713A9CF084DF136" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5DC30F34740CFFF8FC4979EB23D9893" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">Loefling (1758)</bibRefCitation>
is based on the author not agreeing on the inclusion of all elements/species by Linnaeus in his 
<taxonomicName id="E0C90E6908BF7A760C888E8FCD1FA384" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ixia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ixia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2060930824AC8BA13496A08EA72E8FD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ixia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8A62D95412009008F99A7B4AEF607586" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.57996.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481948" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 22" startId="F22">
<paragraph id="83934393C507F5AC19F84E4BAB28C9D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="43CBD170DAB6A7DAF0BA9DA9296C4CBF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2C72F434172C5CF606BD31490EC55775" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium caeruleum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
