<paragraph id="3D2A0BCDC39108CD6AD5CF6BB60E7307" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The first species name to be validly published in 
<taxonomicName id="BB19991E0E277C547419F561C4DC2401" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD4F544630ADF7A8B495CB1C6320FE24" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only proposed almost 20 years later, by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D0F5C86B6A09793E320598327056953" author="Aublet, JBCF" journalOrPublisher="Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Aublet, JBCF, 1775. Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1). Pierre-Francois Didot, London &amp; Paris" title="Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Francoise (Vol. 1)." year="1775">Aublet (1775)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="1CB0EDE7C49ECAEA4DB66F6CF1C8BC55" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="1A03FB9163DB057845C62D13ABCB77D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Aubl. The publication of the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="6BC7B73A548D275C00BC04EDC4066C4F" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FF02B9ACD8BFC0652EB5C83CE5B8ABED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="D73EE1F856A2DE2E87662702E2843962" author="Loefling, P" journalOrPublisher="Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Loefling, P, 1758. Iter Hispanicum. Ttryckt pa Direct &amp; Lars Salvii Kostnad, Stockholm" title="Iter Hispanicum." year="1758">Loefling (1758)</bibRefCitation>
makes it clear that the author recognised a sole species for that genus. The practice of not providing a specific epithet when describing monospecific new genera was common practice at the time. A similar situation, with the description of the type genus of 
<taxonomicName id="D069D63523541FAC0B786E353C32F7D1" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Haemodoraceae</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="86C06C956E2F823C94D13EFD56534588" authorityName="J.E.Smith" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Haemodorum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Haemodorum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BF1622FF2C7A5808B54A22588026CE9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haemodorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CBAA36877F2736E9DB53D168F9015FC7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" author="Smith, JE" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Linnean Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="213 - 223" refId="B57" refString="Smith, JE, 1798. The characters of twenty new genera of plants. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 4 (1): 213 - 223, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" title="The characters of twenty new genera of plants." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" volume="4" year="1798">Smith 1798</bibRefCitation>
) -, supports this interpretation. When first described, 
<taxonomicName id="8811A0185D6CE1EE258E5179394F25B9" authorityName="J.E.Smith" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Haemodorum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Haemodorum" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="80692E26A513F3DD91ADD2C32CFD75E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haemodorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered monospecific and, therefore, was not given a specific epithet, according to the standard practice of J.E. 
<bibRefCitation id="28709824FB9F12152D5D71C649256D3D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" author="Smith, JE" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Linnean Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="213 - 223" refId="B57" refString="Smith, JE, 1798. The characters of twenty new genera of plants. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 4 (1): 213 - 223, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" title="The characters of twenty new genera of plants." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1798.tb00530.x" volume="4" year="1798">Smith (1798)</bibRefCitation>
. Only seven years later, another author (
<bibRefCitation id="56821508063017921C7738553D2A26E1" author="Vahl, M" journalOrPublisher="Moelleri et Filli, Aulae Regiae et Universitatis Typographorum. Impensis Viduae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/545915" refId="B67" refString="Vahl, M, 1805. Martini Vahlii, profess. botan. Haun. membr. societ. lit. plur. Enumeratio Plantarum: vel ab aliis, vel, ab ipso observatum, cum earum differentiis specificis, synonymis selectis et descriptionibus succinctis (Vol. 2). Typis N. Moelleri et Filli, Aulae Regiae et Universitatis Typographorum. Impensis Viduae, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/545915" title="Martini Vahlii, profess. botan. Haun. membr. societ. lit. plur. Enumeratio Plantarum: vel ab aliis, vel, ab ipso observatum, cum earum differentiis specificis, synonymis selectis et descriptionibus succinctis (Vol. 2). Typis N." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/545915" year="1805">Vahl 1805</bibRefCitation>
) provided an epithet for 
<normalizedToken id="82B61E328BF92AE4E431A537C0FC3113" originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
plant, as 
<taxonomicName id="6E0A4ECC68B778B2D0C4A99CBCDDE4E5" genus="H." lsidName="H. corymbosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis id="D2A25ABF93A54593B1D12F1DBB164896" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vahl. Thus, as the first species formally published and associated with 
<taxonomicName id="42F81219C07D07AF9B0575F76080335C" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Xiphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xiphidium" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12901863C3E813606E0D98343FBB5C33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xiphidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="557E67474E67ED9DAB6CECA0B5D1EC58" genus="X." lsidName="X. caeruleum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caeruleum">
<emphasis id="6C5E89FC8638C81EFE4A7BEBA1AF4C04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. caeruleum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
automatically typifies this generic name.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2C6C2DEAA6EB89BBFD51BCCEB97849BE" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.57996.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/481949" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 23" startId="F23">
